A cyclist has been seriously injured in a collision with a car near Possilpark in the north of Glasgow.
Police said the crash happened on Keppochhill Road, near Saracen Street, at about 19:50 on Wednesday.
The 67-year-old man sustained &quot;serious injuries&quot; and was taken to Glasgow Royal Infirmary. No-one else was hurt.
The junction at Keppochhill Road was closed for several hours while police carried out investigations at the scene. The road has since re-opened.
